<paragraph blockId="25.[151,926,1606,1720]" box="[151,926,1698,1720]" pageId="25" pageNumber="26">
<typeStatus box="[151,201,1699,1720]" pageId="25" pageNumber="26">Type</typeStatus>
species 
<taxonomicName authority="Leonardi, 1896" authorityName="Leonardi" authorityYear="1896" box="[287,674,1698,1720]" class="Arachnida" family="Laelapidae" genus="Laelaps" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Mesostigmata" pageId="25" pageNumber="26" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="holothyroides">
<emphasis box="[287,512,1698,1720]" italics="true" pageId="25" pageNumber="26">Laelaps holothyroides</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Leonardi" box="[517,674,1698,1720]" firstAuthor="Leonardi" pageId="25" pageNumber="26" pagination="845 - 882" refId="ref42778" refString="Leonardi, G. (1896) Notizie intorno agli Acaroidei vivente nei Formicai. In: Canestrini, G. (Ed.) Prospetto dell'Acarofauna Italiana, Volume 7, Proserpini, Padova, pp. 845 - 882." type="book chapter" year="1896">Leonardi, 1896</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
, by original designation.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="25.[151,1436,1765,2006]" pageId="25" pageNumber="26">
The original spelling of the name of this genus was 
<taxonomicName authority="(Berlese, 1903 a: 243)" baseAuthorityName="Berlese" baseAuthorityPageNumber="243" baseAuthorityYear="1903" box="[739,1151,1765,1790]" class="Arachnida" family="Pachylaelapidae" genus="Spherolaelaps" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Mesostigmata" pageId="25" pageNumber="26" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[739,898,1765,1790]" italics="true" pageId="25" pageNumber="26">Spherolaelaps</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Berlese" box="[913,1143,1765,1790]" firstAuthor="Berlese" page="243" pageId="25" pageNumber="26" pagination="235 - 252" refId="ref38861" refString="Berlese, A. (1903 a) Acari nuovi. Manipulus I. Redia, 1, 235 - 252." type="journal article" year="1903" yearSuffix="a">Berlese, 1903a: 243</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
. Since then it has always been spelled as 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Berlese" authorityYear="1903" box="[326,491,1801,1826]" class="Arachnida" family="Pachylaelapidae" genus="Sphaerolaelaps" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Mesostigmata" pageId="25" pageNumber="26" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[326,491,1801,1826]" italics="true" pageId="25" pageNumber="26">Sphaerolaelaps</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
or 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Berlese" authorityYear="1903" box="[528,701,1801,1826]" class="Arachnida" family="Pachylaelapidae" genus="Sphaerolaelaps" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Mesostigmata" pageId="25" pageNumber="26" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[528,701,1801,1826]" italics="true" pageId="25" pageNumber="26">Sphaerolaelaps</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, including by Berlese himself. That spelling is maintained here in the interest of stability.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="25.[151,1436,1765,2006]" lastBlockId="26.[151,1436,151,320]" lastPageId="26" lastPageNumber="27" pageId="25" pageNumber="26">
<bibRefCitation author="Berlese" box="[201,381,1873,1898]" firstAuthor="Berlese" pageId="25" pageNumber="26" pagination="235 - 252" refId="ref38861" refString="Berlese, A. (1903 a) Acari nuovi. Manipulus I. Redia, 1, 235 - 252." type="journal article" year="1903" yearSuffix="a">Berlese (1903a)</bibRefCitation>
proposed the new genus 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Berlese" authorityYear="1903" box="[674,847,1873,1898]" class="Arachnida" family="Pachylaelapidae" genus="Sphaerolaelaps" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Mesostigmata" pageId="25" pageNumber="26" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[674,847,1873,1898]" italics="true" pageId="25" pageNumber="26">Sphaerolaelaps</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
with 
<taxonomicName authority="Leonardi, 1896" authorityName="Leonardi" authorityYear="1896" box="[914,1347,1873,1898]" class="Arachnida" family="Laelapidae" genus="Laelaps" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Mesostigmata" pageId="25" pageNumber="26" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="holothyroides">
<emphasis box="[914,1165,1873,1898]" italics="true" pageId="25" pageNumber="26">Laelaps holothyroides</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Leonardi" box="[1174,1347,1873,1898]" firstAuthor="Leonardi" pageId="25" pageNumber="26" pagination="845 - 882" refId="ref42778" refString="Leonardi, G. (1896) Notizie intorno agli Acaroidei vivente nei Formicai. In: Canestrini, G. (Ed.) Prospetto dell'Acarofauna Italiana, Volume 7, Proserpini, Padova, pp. 845 - 882." type="book chapter" year="1896">Leonardi, 1896</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
as 
<typeStatus box="[1388,1436,1874,1898]" pageId="25" pageNumber="26">type</typeStatus>
species, and placed it in the 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Tenorio &amp; Radovsky" baseAuthorityYear="1979" box="[465,592,1909,1934]" class="Arachnida" family="Laelapidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Mesostigmata" pageId="25" pageNumber="26" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="family">Laelapidae</taxonomicName>
. Later, 
<bibRefCitation author="Berlese" box="[673,838,1909,1934]" firstAuthor="Berlese" pageId="25" pageNumber="26" pagination="299 - 474" refId="ref38913" refString="Berlese, A. (1904) Illustrazione iconografica degli Acari mirmecofili. Redia, 1, 299 - 474 + Plates VII - XX." type="journal article" year="1904">Berlese (1904)</bibRefCitation>
placed the genus together with 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Berlese" authorityYear="1888" box="[1194,1345,1909,1934]" class="Arachnida" family="Pachylaelapidae" genus="Pachylaelaps" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Mesostigmata" pageId="25" pageNumber="26" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1194,1345,1909,1934]" italics="true" pageId="25" pageNumber="26">Pachylaelaps</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
into the 
<taxonomicName box="[151,279,1945,1970]" class="Arachnida" family="Gamasidae" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Mesostigmata" pageId="25" pageNumber="26" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="family">Gamasidae</taxonomicName>
. 
<bibRefCitation author="Hirschmann &amp; Krauss" box="[290,624,1945,1970]" firstAuthor="Hirschmann" pageId="25" pageNumber="26" pagination="1 - 5" refId="ref41646" refString="Hirschmann W. &amp; Krauss, W. (1965) Gangsystematik der Parasitiformes. Teil 8. Gamasiden. Bestimmungstafeln von 55 Pachylaelaps - Arten. Acarologie, Schriftenreihe fur vergleichende Milbenkunde, 7, 1 - 5 + Plates 1 - 28." type="journal article" year="1965">Hirschmann &amp; Krauss (1965)</bibRefCitation>
and 
<bibRefCitation author="Karg" box="[680,818,1945,1970]" firstAuthor="Karg" pageId="25" pageNumber="26" pagination="1 - 475" refId="ref42263" refString="Karg, W. (1971) Acari (Acarina), Milben, Unterordnung Anactinochaeta (Parasitiformes). Die freilebenden Gamasina (Gamasides), Raubmilben. Die Tierwelt Deutschlands, 59, 1 - 475." type="journal article" year="1971">Karg (1971)</bibRefCitation>
placed 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Leonardi" baseAuthorityYear="1896" box="[907,1241,1945,1970]" class="Arachnida" family="Pachylaelapidae" genus="Sphaerolaelaps" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Mesostigmata" pageId="25" pageNumber="26" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="holothyroides">
<emphasis box="[907,1241,1945,1970]" italics="true" pageId="25" pageNumber="26">Sphaerolaelaps holothyroides</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Berlese" authorityYear="1888" box="[1278,1429,1945,1970]" class="Arachnida" family="Pachylaelapidae" genus="Pachylaelaps" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Mesostigmata" pageId="25" pageNumber="26" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1278,1429,1945,1970]" italics="true" pageId="25" pageNumber="26">Pachylaelaps</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, but their action has not gained general acceptance. The genus was regarded as valid by 
<bibRefCitation author="Berlese" box="[1139,1319,1981,2006]" firstAuthor="Berlese" pageId="25" pageNumber="26" refId="ref39066" refString="Berlese, A. (1913 a) Acarotheca Italica. Fasciculi Ius et IIus. M. Ricci, Firenze, 221 pp." type="book" year="1913" yearSuffix="a">Berlese (1913a)</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="Vitzthum" firstAuthor="Vitzthum" lastPageId="26" lastPageNumber="27" pageId="25" pageNumber="26" pagination="1 - 55" refId="ref45693" refString="Vitzthum, H. (1931) Resultats Scientifiques du Voyage aux Indes Orientales Neerlandaises. Acarinen. Memoires du Musee Royal d'Histoire Naturelle de Belgique, Hors Serie, 3 (5), 1 - 55." type="journal article" year="1931">Vitzthum (1931)</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="Koroleva" box="[239,440,151,176]" firstAuthor="Koroleva" pageId="26" pageNumber="27" pagination="411 - 483" refId="ref42472" refString="Koroleva, E. V. (1977 b) Family Pachylaelaptidae Vitzthum, 1931. In: Ghilyarov, M. S. &amp; Bregetova, N. G. (Eds) Key to the Soil Inhabiting Mites. Mesostigmata, Nauka, Leningrad, pp. 411 - 483." type="book chapter" year="1977" yearSuffix="b">Koroleva (1977b)</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="Koroleva &amp; Sklyar" box="[451,746,151,176]" firstAuthor="Koroleva" pageId="26" pageNumber="27" pagination="940 - 943" refId="ref42564" refString="Koroleva, E. V. &amp; Sklyar, V. E. (1982) Sphaerolaelaps holothyroides, a new for the fauna of the USSR species of gamasid mites. Zoologicheskii Zhurnal, 61, 940 - 943." type="journal article" year="1982">Koroleva &amp; Sklyar (1982)</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="Moraza &amp; Johnston" box="[757,1060,151,176]" firstAuthor="Moraza" pageId="26" pageNumber="27" pagination="213 - 218" refId="ref43800" refString="Moraza, M. L. &amp; Johnston, D. E. (1990) Pachyseiulus hispanicus n. gen., n. sp., from Navarra (Northern Spain) (Acari: Mesostigmata: Pachylaelapidae). International Journal of Acarology, 16, 213 - 218. http: // dx. doi. org / 10.1080 / 01647959008683870" type="journal article" year="1990">Moraza &amp; Johnston (1990)</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="Karg" box="[1071,1207,151,176]" firstAuthor="Karg" pageId="26" pageNumber="27" pagination="1 - 523" refId="ref42302" refString="Karg, W. (1993) Acari (Acarina), Milben. Parasitiformes (Anactinochaeta). Cohors Gamasina Leach. Raubmilben. 2. Uberarbeitete Auflage. Die Tierwelt Deutschlands, 59, 1 - 523." type="journal article" year="1993">Karg (1993)</bibRefCitation>
and 
<bibRefCitation author="Masan" box="[1261,1432,151,176]" firstAuthor="Masan" pageId="26" pageNumber="27" refId="ref43485" refString="Masan, P. (2007 a) A Review of the Family Pachylaelapidae in Slovakia, with Systematics and Ecology of European Species (Acari: Mesostigmata: Eviphidoidea). Institute of Zoology, Slovak Academy of Sciences, Bratislava, 247 pp." type="book" year="2007" yearSuffix="a">Mašán (2007a)</bibRefCitation>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="26.[151,1436,151,320]" pageId="26" pageNumber="27">This monotypic genus may be recognised by the presence of distinctive modified dorsal setae, which are elongated and thickened, with club-like tips, the atypical position of some dorsal setae, hypertrichous opisthogastric region, the unusual shape of the epistome, bifurcated processes on genu II and tibia II in the male, globular idiosoma, legs longer than the idiosoma, and uniformly setaceous tarsi II, without spur-like distal setae.</paragraph>
